# Recaller

B2B SaaS training execution: ingest content → AI plans (2–10 steps, complexity-based, admin-adjustable) → assign → track completions & behavior → Slack/Teams/email → insights.

## Tech stack

Next.js 16 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind v4, shadcn/ui (nova) · Supabase (Postgres, RLS, pgvector) · Plan AI: **Anthropic** (Claude — analysis) + **OpenAI** (GPT-4.1 generation, GPT-4.1 Mini validation, `text-embedding-3-small` embeddings) · Inngest · Stripe · Resend · Sentry · Slack (@vercel/slack-bolt) · Teams (REST, no BotBuilder) · youtube-transcript, pdf-parse, mammoth; Whisper only when no transcript.

## Build order

0 accounts → 1 schema/auth → 2 content → 3 AI plans → 4 employee UI → 5 manager → 6 Slack → 7 Teams → 8 notifications → 9 billing → 10 insights → 11 calendar → 12 deploy.

## Architecture

- Tenant boundary: `org_id` everywhere.
- NotificationService routes Slack / Teams / email from org + user identity.
- Analytics: pre-written SQL only; AI writes narrative, never ad-hoc production SQL.
- Routes: `src/app/dashboard/*` (admin), `src/app/employee/*` (employees).
- Supabase SSR: browser client, server client + cookies, `src/proxy.ts` for session + route protection (Next.js request proxy).
- **Team & invites:** Admins invite from `/dashboard/team` (Supabase `inviteUserByEmail`, `public.invitations`). Invited users get `user_metadata.invited_org_id`; they complete onboarding at `/employee/setup-password` (sets `password_set_at`) before other employee routes. `/login` handles invite tokens in the URL hash; `/post-login` provisions `public.users`. Team UI lists org members and pending invites; resending marks the previous `pending` invitation `expired`.
- **Plan AI path:** `POST /api/plans/generate` — Claude (Anthropic) analyzes content → OpenAI GPT-4.1 generates the plan → GPT-4.1 Mini validates (with optional regen) → OpenAI embeddings for similarity; see `src/lib/ai/*` and README.

## Trackable steps & proof (aligned with local build guide)

Plans have **2–10** steps (**N** is dynamic — never hardcode 4). **Migration 013+** (see `database-schema.mdc` when added): `plan_steps.proof_type` + `plan_steps.proof_instructions`; `step_completions.evidence` (JSONB); `UNIQUE(assignment_id, step_number)`. **Phase 3:** AI + plan editor produce proof fields; validator treats measurability as including in-app trackability. **Phase 4:** employee submits evidence + `POST /api/completions` (`platform: web`). **Phase 5:** managers see evidence in feeds/history. **Phases 6–7:** Slack/Teams use the **same** completions contract with `platform: slack | teams`. Details: `### Phase 3–8` in **`.cursor/plans/recaller_build_guide_aba69b5a.plan.md`**.

